review_blob: Tastes of Bourbon, toasted malts, vanilla, cocoa, coffee. Good, but not nearly as robust or complex as other BA Stouts. This could probably be related to the low abv. I could easily have a few of these without the alcohol slowing me down.
beer_name: Anderson Valley Wild Turkey Bourbon Barrel Stout

review_blob: Very nice imperial stout as we all have grown to expect from a great Brewer like Founders. One of the best non-BA Stouts Ive had. The perfect blend of coffee, vanilla, cocoa, and maltiness. I could drink this every day.

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: Great Smokey flavor, very sweet. Good for dessert or after dinner. Zero carbonation and absolutely no head or lacing. Very fruity with a touch of molasses. Great sipping brew.
The perfect brew. Beer doesnt get any better than this. Nice cocoa, raisins, chocolate, dark cherry, plum, vanilla. Smooth, delicious and very drinkable.
Poured from can into pint glass. Nice Pale amber color with slight head. Nice hoppyness, citrusy. Decent IPA.
Awesome hop bitterness, piney, woodsey, citrusy, hoppy! Great double Ipa! Nice amber color, nice hoppyness, nice Aroma! Have to try this one!

Dark burgundy in color with slight head and no carbonation. Smell of dark fruits, bananas, raisins. Tastes smooth and fruity like a port wine with a slight alcohol burn on the finish. Excellent example of a Belgian style strong Dark Ale. Very similar to a nice quad. Highly recommend this beer.

Possibly the best beer in the world. This beer definitely shows the Brewers expertise and craftsmanship. Tastes of smooth dark sweet fruits. Plums, raisins, dark cherries. Compares to, yet better than the most extravagant of wines. After a heavenly palatable experience, a smooth Smokey alcohol like finish. Very pleasurable indeed. Quite orgasmic in its complexity. Kudos to this Brewer!

Beautiful Reddish brown color with a little head. Nice cherry arroma. Tastes very very sweet. Like decadent sweet fruits or a fine wine. Maybe just a little too sweet for my taste. Deap alcohol burn on the finish. This beer makes a great lead in as it prepares your Palate for your favorite Belgian Quad.

Pours a nice medium amber. Slight head with some lacing that hangs around for a while. Smells like pine. Tastes woodsy and sweet with a nice bitter aftertaste of a good Ipa but a surprisingly excellent following of the honey. Unlike other crafts, this brew tastes better at extremely cold temperature. Love this beer. One of my favorite IPAs.

Very nice dark fruity flavors, grapes, Plums, raisins. Nice alcohol burn... very inviting, like a barrel aged quad. Tastes of vanilla, hints of chocolate, and toffee. Aroma is beautiful and pleasureful. Malt complexity of a well crafted Belgian brew. I love this beer and it only gets better with age.

Taste just like a pils. Miller lite definitely comes to mind. I love IPAs and DIPAs but this is not one of the good or even average ones. Had to lick the dogs Butt to get the taste out of my mouth. My score was generous.

Small single finger head. No carbonation. Very little lacing that disappears almost immediately. Black as used motor oil. Smells of alcohol, dark roasted malts, vanilla, molasses, and cocoa. Tastes of coffee, chocolate, molasses, roasted malts, burnt wood, and alcohol. Some alcohol burn on the roof of the mouth and back of the tongue. Good Stout, but not quite outstanding.
UPDATED: JAN 9, 2014

Pours a great dark brownish black with virtually no head. Aroma of coffee and Dark chocolate and a little bourbon alcohol. Taste is creamy dark chocolate and brewed sumatran, barely any bourbon flavor. Kudos to Epic for an epic beer.
UPDATED: JAN 10, 2014

Poured from a bottle into a nice snifter, nice black color with a low tan head. Aroma of smoky roasted coffee, chocolate, vanilla. Nose cant pick up any of the chili peppers cleverly disguised beneath. Tastes of exceptionally balanced creamy mocha coffee and vanilla with just a bit of caramel. Slight alcohol on the finish.  Still the peppers lie to you with their camouflage inside other complexities. Then as the first half glass disappears and without warning from the depths of my soul and gradually creaping up to the back of my tongue comes the burn. Not an intense pepper burn, just enough to let you know its there. Its as If I was suddenly revisited by a previously consumed stuffed poblano. It made my palate cry out "hell yeah!" and left me wanting more as I suddenly realize the genius behind it all. Well balanced, great beer!
UPDATED: JAN 11, 2014

Poured from a refrigerated bottle into a pint glass. Dark Reddish brown with a  slight tan head. Aroma of toasted breads, malts, and sweet maple syrup. Taste up front was sweet and delightful with some scotch coming through. Hints of vanilla and maple syrup or molasses and a smoky malt complexity. Thick to drink but very good and very creamy.

Color is a medium dark translucent amber. Smells of fresh oranges and hops. Taste of bitterness like an IPA. Pine, spruce and citrus flavor with very nice hoppyness. Very drinkable, gets better with each and every sip. Gets you wanting another and another. Best served at about 45 degrees. Very good APA from 3 floyds. Better than Zombie Dust in my opinion.
UPDATED: JAN 10, 2014
Nice floral hop aroma. Taste like a typical Ipa only better than most. Near perfect balance of hops and sweetness. Great beer. Recommended for all you hop heads.
beer_name: Cigar City Jai Alai India Pale Ale

review_blob: UPDATED: JAN 10, 2014
UPDATED: JAN 8, 2014
beer_name: Gouden Carolus Cuvee Van De Keizer Blauw/Blue

review_blob: UPDATED: JAN 5, 2014

Color deap amber to Reddish brown. Smell of dark fruit and ripe bananas. Taste in a word, heavenly! Nice dark fruitiness, dark cherries, raisins, Plums, grapes. Very sweet like exquisite candy. A little alcohol burn but not too much. One of the best Belgians I have tasted.

Reddish brown color, nice cherry dark grape wine smell. Light carbonation, very pleasant on the back of the tongue. Taste of the sweetest dark cherries, raisins, Plums. Every sip made me desire another. Heavenly.
UPDATED: FEB 19, 2014
